meanings.definition: To earn more money than (someone or something)
meanings.sent1: Last month, the new movie outgrossed all the others at the box office.
meanings.sent2: The popular restaurant outgrossed its competitors by offering unique dishes.
meanings.sent3: The little lemonade stand outgrossed the big coffee shop in sales!
meanings.sent4: Her determination to succeed outgrossed any obstacles in her way.
meanings.sent5: The student's lemonade stand outgrossed all expectations, making him the talk of the town.

meanings.definition: To exceed in total sales or revenue
meanings.sent1: The tech company outgrossed its projections for the quarter.
meanings.sent2: The new product line outgrossed the previous year's sales by a significant margin.
meanings.sent3: The bakery outgrossed the nearby grocery store in pastry sales.
meanings.sent4: Her talent for marketing outgrossed her colleagues' efforts.
meanings.sent5: The team's hard work outgrossed their competitors, securing them the top spot in the market.
